content.text:
I cannot access the web or perform real-time searches in this sandboxed environment (bash tool lacks internet connectivity). 

The US penny (one-cent coin) is still actively minted by the US Mint, with over 3 billion produced in fiscal year 2023 alone, and production continuing into 2024. There is no "last" penny minted to date, as it's ongoing for circulation and collectors.

If you mean the last 95% copper composition penny, it was October 22, 1982 (San Francisco Mint), or 1982-10-22 format. Confirm via official sources for precision.

The working directory is the project root.
